# ANTI-SLOP FRONTEND RULES
# Scope: Design Engineering (UI, UX, Visual Systems, Components)
# This file governs everything visual. No exceptions.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
I. FUNDAMENTAL PRINCIPLES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Nothing generic.
- Nothing hardcoded.
- Nothing "pretty by default".
- Nothing that looks like a template, boilerplate, or AI output.
- Everything must look designed by a professional with graphic criteria.

Every visual decision must:
- Have intention.
- Be justified.
- Be aligned with a system.
- Be reproducible and scalable.

If something exists "because it looks good", it is removed.
If something exists "because it's always done this way", it is removed.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
II. ACTIVATION OF THESE RULES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

These rules are activated when requesting:
- UI, frontend, web, landing, dashboard, page, component.
- Styling, layout, spacing, colors, fonts, motion.
- "Beautify", "improve UI", "design", "polish", "make it nicer".

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
III. DESIGN SYSTEM (MANDATORY)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Every visual value must come from the Design System.
- No magic values allowed.
- No isolated decisions allowed.

MANDATORY:
- Colors from tokens.
- Typography from tokens.
- Spacing from tokens.
- Radii from tokens.
- Z-index from tokens.
- Motion from tokens.

FORBIDDEN:
- Hex colors.
- Arbitrary px.
- Fonts directly in CSS.
- Improvised gradients.
- Shadows copied from examples.

If a token does not exist → do not use it.
If needed → propose via system, not inline.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
IV. AESTHETICS (ANTI-GENERIC)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Every interface must have a CLEAR AESTHETIC DIRECTION.

Before writing code:
- Define a dominant visual axis.
- Choose a character (e.g., editorial, brutalist, industrial, organic, technical, luxurious, experimental).
- Commit to that direction.

FORBIDDEN:
- Neutral aesthetics.
- "Clean UI" without character.
- Predictable layouts.
- Generic card grids.
- Hero + 3 columns + CTA.

Every screen must be recognizable without reading the content.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
V. TYPOGRAPHY (REAL DESIGN CRITERIA)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Typography is structure, not decoration.
- Each project defines a clear hierarchy.

RULES:
- Maximum 2 font families.
- One display with character.
- One functional and legible body.
- All defined in tokens.

FORBIDDEN:
- Inter
- Roboto
- Arial
- System UI
- Space Grotesk by default

Any new typography requires:
- Documented license.
- Legibility proof.
- Contrast test.
- Usage rationale.

There is no "pretty font".
There is the correct typography for the system.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VI. COLOR (SYSTEM, NOT TASTE)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Color communicates hierarchy and state.
- It is not "chosen", it is designed.

RULES:
- One dominant color.
- Limited accents.
- Neutrals with intention.

FORBIDDEN:
- Timid palettes.
- Generic gradients.
- Purple on white.
- Uncontrolled saturation.

Adjustments:
- Lighten/Darken maximum ±15%.
- Overlays only with tokens.
- Gradients only combining existing tokens.

Every color must have a clear semantic function.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VII. LAYOUT, GRID AND SPACE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Layout defines the product's character.

RULES:
- Spacing only from tokens.
- Explicit grid (even if broken).
- Decide: controlled density OR generous space.

ALLOWED:
- Asymmetry.
- Overlap.
- Diagonals.
- Intentional grid-breaking.

FORBIDDEN:
- Alignments by habit.
- Automatic symmetry.
- Padding "just because".

Empty space is a decision, not a residue.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VIII. COMPONENTS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Components are not widgets, they are system pieces.

RULES:
- Use existing components before creating new ones.
- Do not modify base components.
- Extend only by composition.
- One component = one clear visual responsibility.

FORBIDDEN:
- Duplicating components with minimal variations.
- "Wrapper" components without visual logic.
- Infinite cosmetic props.

If a component grows uncontrollably, it is redesigned.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
IX. FLEX, STACKS AND FLOW
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Flexbox and layout are not utilities, they are structure.

RULES:
- Flex only when flow requires it.
- Stacks defined by system.
- Gap from tokens, never arbitrary.

FORBIDDEN:
- display:flex by default.
- Visual adjustments based on trial & error.
- Systematic align-center.

Every axis has intention: horizontal or vertical, never ambiguous.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
X. MOTION AND MICRO-INTERACTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Motion communicates hierarchy and rhythm.

RULES:
- Maximum 1–2 high-impact moments per view.
- Motion must reinforce narrative, not decorate.
- Prefer native CSS.

FORBIDDEN:
- Constant animations.
- Generic transitions.
- Default easing without criteria.

Every animation must be justifiable verbally.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
XI. ACCESSIBILITY (NOT OPTIONAL)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Aesthetics do not justify inaccessibility.

RULES:
- Minimum WCAG contrast.
- Semantic HTML.
- Keyboard navigation.
- Visible states.

If something breaks accessibility:
- It is redesigned.
- It is not "compensated".

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
XII. MANDATORY DELIVERY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

All frontend output must include:
- Functional code.
- Explicit use of tokens.
- Declared aesthetic direction.
- Clear typographic hierarchy.
- Justified layout decisions.
- Zero hardcoded values.
- Zero generic elements.

If it does not meet all the above, IT IS NOT FINISHED.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
XIII. AUTOMATIC DELETION CRITERIA
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Anything is removed that:
- Is generic.
- Is not in the system.
- Has no clear intention.
- Only "beautifies".
- Could exist in any other product.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
END OF FILE
